-- Piramal Real Estate Fund May Pay 6 Billion Rupees for Mumbai Mall, ET Says
-- Suprotip Ghosh
-- 2010-07-14T01:55:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/piramal-real-estate-fund-may-pay-6-billion-rupees-for-mumbai-mall-et-says.html

          
          
             An Indian real estate fund
controlled by the Piramal family, owners of Piramal Healthcare
Ltd., may pay six billion rupees ($128 million) for a majority
stake in the company that owns SoBo Central, a Mumbai shopping
mall, from Future Group, owner of India’s biggest publicly-
traded retailer, the Economic Times reported, citing people it
didn’t identify.  
